NexusRecon is reconnaissance tooling for authorized red-team and
penetration-testing engagements. It enforces engagement scope at the
framework level, every tool invocation is validated against a signed
scope file before execution. Operators using this software outside
that intended use are exposing themselves to civil and criminal
liability under computer-fraud statutes in nearly every jurisdiction
(CFAA in the US, Computer Misuse Act in the UK, EU Directive 2013/40,
and equivalents).

The maintainers do not provide support to operators who cannot
demonstrate written authorization for the target of their use. Bug
reports, feature requests, and general questions remain welcome from
everyone.

