Third-Party Components
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

NexusRecon orchestrates and depends on many third-party libraries and
external services. Their respective licenses apply to their code; see
each project's LICENSE for terms. Notable categories:

  • Python libraries (CrewAI, LangGraph, LangChain, httpx, structlog,
    Pydantic, Textual, Typer, etc.)
  • CLI binaries the framework wraps (subfinder, amass, dnsx, httpx,
    nuclei, katana, arjun, gitleaks, trufflehog, gowitness, gau,
    maigret, theHarvester)
  • External API services (Shodan, Censys, VirusTotal, GreyNoise,
    SecurityTrails, Hunter.io, HIBP, GitHub, Crunchbase, FullHunt,
    BinaryEdge, Netlas, ZoomEye, AbuseIPDB, LeakIX, IntelX, OTX,
    Chaos, IPinfo, urlscan, Censys, Wayback Machine, KEV, EPSS,
    NVD, OSV, GitHub Advisory DB, Vulners, Hudson Rock, EmailRep,
    LeakCheck, Wikipedia, SEC EDGAR, Adzuna, Bing, and others)

Use of each external API is governed by that provider's terms of
service. The framework does not modify or redistribute upstream API
responses; it parses them for use in the operator's authorized
engagement.
